{"id":"2209.13419","submitter":"Min He","authors":"Min He and Ralf Rapp","title":"Bottom hadro-chemistry in high-energy hadronic collisions","comments":"6 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-ph hep-ex nucl-ex nucl-th","license":"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/","abstract":"  The hadro-chemistry of bottom quarks ($b$) produced in hadronic collisions\nencodes valuable information on the mechanism of color-neutralization in these\nreactions. Since the $b$-quark mass is much larger than the typical hadronic\nscale of $\\sim$1\\,GeV, the $b\\bar b$ pair production is expected to be well\nseparated from their subsequent hadronization process. In particular, a\nsignificantly larger fraction of $b$ baryons has been observed in proton-proton\n($pp$) and proton-antiproton ($p\\bar{p}$) reactions relative to that measured\nin $e^+e^-$ collisions, posing a challenge to theoretical descriptions. We\npropose to resolve this problem by employing a statistical hadronization\napproach with a largely augmented set of $b$-hadron states beyond the currently\nmeasured spectrum as listed by the particle data group, by using guidance from\nthe relativistic quark model and lattice-QCD compuations. Assuming {\\it\nrelative} chemical equilibrium between the yields of different kinds of $b$\nhadrons, their thermo-statistical densities are used as fragmentation weights\nof a $b$-quarks into the various hadron species. Aided by quark model estimates\nof the decay systematics of excited states, the fragmentation fractions of\nweakly-decaying $b$ hadrons are computed and found to agree well with\nmeasurements in $p\\bar{p}$ collisions at the Tevatron. Employing\ntransverse-momentum ($p_T$) distributions of $b$-quarks from perturbative QCD\nand combining thermo-statistical fragmentation weights with independent\nfragmentation toward high $p_T$, we deduce the total $b\\bar{b}$ cross section\nbased on the computed hadro-chemistry. At the same time a fair description of\nthe $\\bar{B}_s^0/B^-$ and $\\Lambda_b^0/B^-$ ratios measured in $pp$ collisions\nat the LHC is obtained. Our study thus corroborates the statistical nature of\n$b$-quark hadronization in hadronic collisions at collider energies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Sep 2022 14:18:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-28"}
