nger data augmentations and nearest neighbors. Second, we construct a set\nof objectives that encourage the model to be capable of decomposing medical\nimages into a collection of anatomical features in an unsupervised manner.\nLastly, we both empirically and theoretically, demonstrate the efficacy of our\nMONA on three benchmark datasets with different labeled settings, achieving new\nstate-of-the-art under different labeled semi-supervised settings\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Sep 2022 15:50:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2022 20:19:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Nov 2022 08:09:18 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 23:04:33 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 17 Mar 2023 00:41:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-20"}
