er hand, the intermediate disorder\nlimit of the partition function, when it exists, is universal: it is expressed\nas a chaos expansion of iterated integrals against a Gaussian\nprocess~$\\mathcal{M}$, which arises as the scaling limit of the field\n$(e^{\\beta V(\\hat\\omega_i,\\bar\\omega_j)})_{i,j\\geq 0}$ and exhibits strong\ncorrelations on lines and columns.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Sep 2022 15:54:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-28"}
